        seconds. It requires no sign-up, no installation, and no data sharing
        &mdash; it uses the browser's native <code>event.repeat</code> property
        to distinguish genuine key presses from operating-system auto-fires.
        From checking the <strong>windows 11 key repeat rate</strong> to
        confirming your <strong>key repeat rate mac</strong> setting, this is a
        clear, trustworthy way to understand your keyboard's true behavior.
      </p>
